sub_topic: Identifying the isomorphism between two graphs.
message_1: Consider two graphs G and H, where G has 6 vertices and 7 edges, and H has 6 vertices and 6 edges. Determine whether or not G and H are isomorphic.
message_2: G and H cannot be isomorphic because they have different numbers of edges. Isomorphic graphs must have the same number of vertices and edges, as well as the same degree sequence. Since G has 7 edges and H has 6 edges, they cannot be isomorphic.
